parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical wire harness can cause a fire hazard, leading to property damage or personal injury. It can also result in the failure of various vehicle systems, including the blower motor, which can affect the vehicle's overall performance and safety.
symptoms: Melted electrical wires
failure of the blower switch
and potentially other electrical system failures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brakes lock up and do not release
brakes do not slow the vehicle
vehicle crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and violent vibration of the front end, also known as the "death wobble," can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-miss incidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle vibrates violently while driving
often triggered by hitting a bump in the road
regardless of size; the vibration can be intense and unpredictable
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of body mounts can cause severe body roll, harsh ride, and noise, leading to compromised vehicle handling and safety. In extreme cases, it can lead to radiator damage, and potentially, separation of the body from the chassis in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Harsh ride
body roll
popping and screeching noise from underneath the vehicle
radiator damage
and cracking of the radiator casing.
